dataIdInfo.idAbs:
Rail Stations for both current (red line) and new rail lines open May 2015.

Additions include platforms that exist on the new green and purple line which are scheduled to be in revenue generating operation in May 2015. Platforms are used to depict the exact location of boarding and alighting Metro rail system based on the desired direction of travel; eastbound (EB), westbound (WB), northbound (NB), or southbound (SB). Platforms reflect the locations as they exist today geographically.
dataIdInfo.idPurp: Locations for boarding or alighting the Houston METRO rail system. This data is used for map display, query and analysis in Geographic Information System (GIS) software. Rail platform locations are used for on-board stop announcements, ridership counts by stop, METRO and Google Trip Planners, and the METRO Customer Information Center.

prcStep.stepDesc: Routes Discontinued - 35 Fairview, 39 Parker, 48 W Dallas, 60 Hardy, 286 W Little York/NWTC/Greenway P&R, 313 Allen Parkway Shuttle Routes Restructured - 18 Kirby (replace 313), 37 El Sol, 48 Navigation (Magnolia TC Trips), 58 Hammerly (48 W Dallas), 67 Dairy Ashford (Original North end Configuration), 70 Memorial (48 W Dallas), 97 Settegast (All trips to Dividend @ Currency), 132 Harwin (Shift service from Holman to Elgin in Midtown)

Major updates include route restructure for West or North ends of routes 36 46 58. Also route change for routes 29 and 80 due to the closing of Tierwester on TSU campus. Restructure of route 75 to become the Eldridge Crosstown. The 67 Dairy Ashford is extended to serve the Addicks Park & Ride. Routes 52 and 87 were restructured on their Southern ends.
